Do a global search for a substring that contains a sequence of at least three digits:

Copy
let str = "100, 1000 or 10000?";
let patt1 = /\d{3,}/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The n{X,} quantifier matches any string that contains a sequence of at least X n's.

X must be a number.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
{X,}	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("n{X,}") or simply: /n{X,}/
Syntax with modifiers
Copy
new RegExp("n{X,}", "g") or simply: /\n{X,}/g
